### GoDaam local API — use with VS Code "REST Client" or similar extensions
### Start stack: npm run dev (repo root GoDaam) — API :3001; web UI is usually http://localhost:5173/
### If Vite says "Port 5173 is in use", open the printed URL (e.g. http://localhost:5175/).
@base = http://localhost:3001
@token = REPLACE_WITH_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN

### Health (no auth)
GET {{base}}/api/health

### Login — default local admin matches backend/.env (admin / admin123)
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"admin","password":"admin123"}

### Example authenticated call (paste token from login response)
GET {{base}}/api/dashboard/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
